title: Trader Joe's Speculoos Crunchy Cookie Butter Set of 4
description: Trader Joe's Speculoos Crunchy Cookie Butter is, in its most simplistic terms, spreadable Speculoos cookies. Speculoos cookies are classic Belgian cookies with great crunch, and a slightly caramelized, almost-but-not-quite-gingerbread flavor. (Try our Bistro Biscuits for a close approximation.) After the cookies are baked to a fabulous finish, they're crushed into a fine powder and mixed with magical ingredients (read: vegetable oils) and turned into a smooth, spreadable substance we call Cookie Butter. It resembles peanut butter in color and consistency. Make no mistake, though; this is a treat through and through. Spread it on toast, bagels, pancakes or waffles. Use it as a dip for hunks of dark chocolate or pretzels or (gasp!) veggies like carrots or celery. You could keep it really simple and just use it as a dip for a spoon.

title: Lucky Brand Jerky Original Protein Stick Jerky Box, 5-Ounce
description: Nebraska Star Beef Lucky Beef Original Jerky Sticks use beef used raised with no antibiotics and no growth hormones. Nebraska Star Beef Lucky Brand Natural Angus beef jerky is made in small batches - they never exceed 200 lbs. - by skilled artisans right here in Nebraska. They grow all of their own beef so you know that you're getting a consistent, quality product from a local business that cares about what they sell. Original flavor is their own special blend of spices, premium sea salt and a secret ingredient that gives Original a little extra zip without adding heat. This is Nebraska Star Beef's best selling flavor by a wide margin. These Beef Sticks are a ground and formed product that come in a generous 4 ounce bag. Nebraska Star Beef is processed, wet aged 35 days, cut, flash frozen and stored in a state of the art frozen storage facility until it ships to you in a cooler with dry ice. Nebraska Star Beef meets all state and federal requirements for safety and takes safety a step further by building a frozen product that is designed to be frozen from the ground up - never steaks that have been on the butcher counter until they HAD to be frozen - this adds an extra margin of safety and also improves quality. This is a product that they make to feed their family; rest assured that safety will never be compromised when you serve Nebraska Star Beef products to your family.

title: Blue Diamond Growers - Almond Breeze Almond Milk Unsweetened Vanilla - 32 oz.
description: Blue Diamond Growers - Almond Breeze Almond Milk Unsweetened - Vanilla - 32 FL OZ (1 QT) 946 mL Blue Diamond Growers Almond Breeze Almond Milk Unsweetened Vanilla, the unsweetened version of Almond Breeze Original, still provides a touch of the almond's natural sweetness, but eliminates the added sugar.  After Blue Diamond Growers introduced Almond Breeze, they got many requests from customers to bring out a sugar-free version. So they did just that. Almond Breeze is a non-dairy beverage made from real almonds, all natural, smooth and creamy with a hint of almonds. Almond Breeze is a great tasting non-dairy beverage without the thin, chalky after taste of rice and soy beverages.Enjoy Almond Breeze chilled by the glass and on your cereal. You will love how it froths in coffee drinks, enhances fruit smoothies, and blends cup for cup in your favorite recipes. Gluten, cholesterol and lactose free Excellent source of calcium, vitamins D & E Good source of vitamin A A refreshing alternative to soy and rice non-dairy beverages Calcium enriched Almond Breeze, available in Original, Chocolate, Vanilla, and Unsweetened Vanilla has no saturated fat, no cholesterol, and half the calories of 1% milk. Almond Breeze FAQs Is an unsweetened Almond Breeze available?Yes. Blue Diamond offers Unsweetened Almond Breeze in a variety of flavors and sizes, which provide the same flavorful taste with lower calories.What flavors of Almond Breeze are available?Blue Diamond offers Almond Breeze in Original, Vanilla, and Chocolate flavors as well as our new Almondmilk Coconutmilk blends. Can Almond Breeze be used for baking and in recipes?Almond Breeze can be used in most recipes requiring dairy milk. Almond Breeze does not work with packaged instant puddings. Does Almond Breeze contain any dairy ingredients?No.  All Almond Breeze products are dairy-free.  They do not contain lactose or casein.

title: Newman's Own Organics Newman-O's Creme Filled Chocolate Cookies Wheat Free -- 8 oz
description: <B><i>Newman's Own Organics Organic Wheat Free/Dairy Free Vanilla Cream Cookie-O's</i></b><P><br>Nell Newman loves chocolate and can't go too long without dreaming up a new use for it. This time it's Newman-O's Wheat Free/Dairy Free Vanilla Creme cookies, rich chocolaty cookie sandwiches with creamy vanilla filling. These cookies are made without wheat or dairy ingredient, which makes for delicious snacking without the worry of food allergens.<P>And with Newman's O's, you don't have to worry about where the products come from, either. All Newman's O's chocolate cookies include organic cacao that comes from small farmers in the Talamanca region on the Atlantic coast of Costa Rica and Panama. Some of these farms provide important buffer zones for the La Amistad Biosphere Reverse, a habitat for endangered mammal and bird species. Methods of farming and harvesting are used that do not require the destruction of the rain forests.<p>Newman's Organics sources their organic chocolate from producers in Central and South America. Their producers take measures to certify that all of the cocoa they purchase is produced without the use of forced labor. Their group of cooperatives are inspected to verify compliance with organic standards. They require written verification from the inspector that each farm is "slavery-free." <P>*Not Gluten Free

title: Somersaults - Crunchy Nuggets Sunflower Seed Snacks Cinnamon Crunch - 6 oz.
description: Somersaults Crunchy Nuggets Sunflower Seed Snacks Cinnamon Crunch - 6 Pack(s) Somersaults Cinnamon Crunch bakes warm cinnamon into thier whole wheat dough to create a delightful yet healthy treat. A little sprinkle of sweetness makes this perfect crunchy snack a coffee pairing delight! With just 7g of sugar (that's 42% less than a granola bar!), this treat is a good-for-you twist on Grandma's home baked cinnamon rolls. Cinnamon is a great source of fiber, iron, and calcium! Somersaults Crunchy Nuggets Sunflower Seed Snacks Cinnamon Crunch is made with: Cinnamon: Highly prized among ancient nations this exotic spice is obtained from the inner bark of the cinnamon tree, native to South East Asia. Its flavor comes from an aromatic essential oil, baked into our Cinnamon Crunch it balances out the sweet nutty flavor. Molasses: To make molasses, the cane of a sugar plant is harvested and stripped of its leaves. Its juice is extracted usually by crushing or mashing and then boiled to a concentrate to promote crystallization. Sunflower Seeds: Those beautiful, sunny yellow flowers lining the fields on many cross-country road trips are the source of our scrumptious sunflower seeds. As the #1 ingredient in Somersaults, these kernels are an excellent source of protein! Whole Wheat Flour: From sea to shining sea, we capture the whole grains of sun-kissed wheat to provide a more nutritious alternative to refined white flour. Sesame Seeds: From sea to shining sea, we capture the whole grains of sun-kissed wheat to provide a more nutritious alternative to refined white flour. Sunflower Oil: High oleic sunflower oil is one of the most natural and healthy oils that can be used in the baking process. It has the highest monounsaturated oleic acid content (80%) of any commercially available cooking/salad oil, including olive oil! Evaporated Cane Juice: This all-natural sweetener derived from the sugar cane plant provides a healthy alternative to refined sugar.

description: Box of 12 - 100 calorie snack packs of in-shell roasted and perfectly sea-salted pistachios. Nature’s Joy all-natural California pistachios come from our growers to you. We have been growing pistachios in California's san Joaquin valley for over 20 years. Sustainably farmed, heart-healthy and packed with vitamins and minerals your body needs to stay healthy. Pistachios alleviate stress, aid in weight management, promote post-workout recovery and help sustain a healthy love life. One serving of pistachios has as much potassium (300 mg, 8%) as an orange (250 mg, 7%). Pistachios contain more than 10% of the daily value of dietary fiber and essential vitamins and minerals like b6, thiamin, copper and phosphorus. You can obtain about as much dietary fiber from a serving of pistachios (2.9 gram, 12%) as from a ½ cup cooked broccoli (2.5 gram, 10%). Pistachios are a naturally cholesterol free snack that contain 1.5 gram of saturated fat. Pistachios, with 6 gram of protein, are considered part of the protein group according to the USDA my plate. Pistachios, like olive oil, primarily contain monounsaturated fat. The dietary guidelines for Americans recommend you get most of your fats from sources of polyunsaturated and monounsaturated fatty acids. A one-ounce serving of pistachios equals about 49 nuts – more per serving than any other snack nut. Pistachios contain several antioxidants. Pistachios have the perfect gastronomic attributes – color, texture and crunch – a perfect ingredient for sweet and savory dishes. Our processing plant is an established industry leader for environmentally-friendly and sustainable nut processing and farming-practices. We are dedicated to sustainable processes and methodologies as an integral part of our culture.

description: Mixed pack of 6 Different Exceptional Teas including such flavors as Peppermint & English toffee, Valley of the Kings Ceylon Pekoe, ACAI Berry Pomegranate & Vanilla, Arabian Mint Tea with Honey, Italian Almond, and Berry Sensation. Each box contains 20 tea bags each. --- ABOUT THE BRAND --- Some years ago, Americans drank mainly Ceylon Tea, the world's finest. Today, almost any brand you buy is a multi-origin blend that is a mix of teas from several countries. Dilmah, new to the U.S, is the number one brand of authentic, garden fresh Single Origin Ceylon tea in over 90 countries. Dilmah is Single Origin, 100% Pure Ceylon, entirely grown, handpicked & packaged in Ceylon (now Sri Lanka), producer of the world's finest tea. Single Origin explains why Dilmah is fresher, richer and full of flavor. Discerning tea drinkers will recognize the distinct difference in the very first sip. Dilmah is Packed at Source, Garden Fresh. Packaging in Sri Lanka, within days of picking fresh leaf in the tea fields, maximizes freshness, the key to antioxidants in tea. Founder Merrill J. Fernando is the most senior master tea taster today and his face appears on every pack of Dilmah tea, as his personal guarantee of the quality and freshness of Dilmah. Dilmah is Traditionally Manufactured. Ordinary teas have abandoned the centuries' old orthodox method of manufacture for the fast track CTC (cut twist curl) process, to meet demand for a quicker brew from tea bags. This has sacrificed the character and real taste of tea. Dilmah stands firmly by traditional tea making methods, which explains why Dilmah tea tastes so different. Dilmah is the world's first truly ethical tea. It is the only international brand name owned by tea growers. We pack our tea shelf ready, right where it is grown. Earnings therefore remain in Sri Lanka for the benefit of our workers. Visit www.mjffoundation.org and Dilmah.com to learn more.

Just a pinch of this decadent salt will bring out the subtle notes in any dish from creamy poached eggs to buttery mashed potatoes, rich marinades and even the simple joy of popcorn! You can turn anything into a work of art with this tasteful and time-honored elegant salt.

title: Black Truffle Smoked Mushroom Powder - 100% Pure & Unrefined! (1 oz (1/16 lb))
description: Shop Where Top Chef's Shop!nCold Stored in our Climate/Light Controlled Rooms!nThe Finest Dried Truffle on the Market!nAmazing smoky, mouth-watering essence of the Smoked Truffle Powder is here at Florida Herb House! Black Truffles (Tuber Melanosporum) are the most famous Truffles in the world. The flavor of a Truffle is pervasive in a subtle way; this enigma of taste is one of the reasons that Truffles have such a loyal following amongst food lovers. Much folklore has arisen around Truffles the tales of pigs and dogs which can find them, or flies that hover above Truffles. In any event, Truffles have created a following and a folklore because they are a delicious, interesting fungi.nnSmoked Truffle PowdernThe same savory character of the Classic Black Truffle, with a perfectly balanced hint of smoky flavor. Add to any dish, stock, butter, and oil to create a deliciously smoky, earthy element.nn100% Black Winter Truffle Powder (Tuber melanosporum)nCertified organic, Kosher, International OrganicnAvailable year-roundnThree-year shelf lifen100% dry weight powdernnSuggested Use - The flavor of Truffles should be allowed center stage in most dishes. Truffle Powder can be used sparingly because of its potency. Truffle Powder is wonderful in soups and sauces, particularly those which utilize White Wine or Champagne and are served with pasta.nnBasic Preparations - Truffle powder is ready to use as an ingredient with no preparation necessary.nnFlorida Herb House dried truffle mushroom powder will last much longer than the extremely perishable fresh truffle. When they are dried the flavor of the truffle is concentrated because of the removal of excess water content. Remember, a small amount of truffle powder will go a long way. When the truffle powder is heated the aroma and flavors are released. Renowned for it's aroma, the black truffle can be described as intense, aromatic and fruity.

description: Farm Fresh Goodness from Our Kitchen to Yours!At Sweet Home Farm, we are dedicated to farm fresh goodness and down home value. In fact, we've been making our simply delicious granola for more than 15 years, choosing only the finest all natural whole grains, fruits and nuts, with simple sweeteners and a bit of spice just to keep things interesting. The ingredients are grown and made without GMOs, and no preservatives, artificial flavors, or artificial colors ever get anywhere near the granolas. Then we pack as much goodness as we can fit into the signature milk carton to give you plenty of great value too. So, take tip from the folks at Sweet Home Farm and make this honestly good, naturally delicious granola part of your day! The Amazing American PecanA member of the hickory family, the Pecan tree grows over 100 feet tall and bears nuts for more than 300 year. The pecan is the state nut of Alabama, the state tree of Texas and the only nut native to North America (aside from Lucille Ball and Abbott & Costello). Breakfast AmericanaProducing maple syrup is the oldest agriculture enterprise in North America; the cultivation of pecans in the Deep South dates back to pre-Colonial times. We've combined these classic American flavors with crunchy oat clusters to create a truly scrumptious granola. Nutritious whole rolled oats give you energy and fiber to start the day right, while velvety rich pecans provide protein and essential unsaturated fats. title: Tartuflanghe (2 pack) Truffle Cream Black 30g From Italy
description: Made from Black summer truffle (tuber aestivum) 99% and olive oil, these truffle creams are a very concentrated product. They are authentic truffle pures, ideal to enrich your warm dishes, such as pasta, risotti, eggs and meat fillets. They are prepared by mixing the truffle with olive oil, without adding any other ingredients, so that they are able to offer you a really genuine product.nThe company founders, Domenica and Beppe, began business in the world of the truffle in 1968, selling fresh truffles from Piedmont. During those years, their restaurant Da Beppe, in the heart of Alba town, was designated by the Michelin guide as a reference point for lovers of cooking based on mushrooms and truffles.nnTartuflanghe was founded in 1980 in order to profit from Beppe's inspiration and culinary experience which had matured following a prestigious career: Head Chef aboard cruise ships from 1958 - 1966, teacher in a catering school, chef in the most well known restaurants of Piedmontese cuisine and then owner of his famous restaurant.nnThe first truffle specialities were created to give aficionados the opportunity to enjoy good cooking and also truffles out of season. Thanks to this policy the kitchen laboratories of Tartuflanghe produced the first truffle pasta product in the world (awarded best new product of the year prize in 1992 at the Fancy Food Summer Show in New York). After tagliolini pasta with truffle came prepared risotto, polenta and fonduta with truffle. Beppe's traditional, very authentic Piedmontese recipes have enabled the company to become established in the specialized high quality gastronomic product market right from the start.nnTartuflanghe today is to be found in the most prestigious shops and gourmet outlets in Italy. Their truffle specialities are, moreover, appreciated in top class restaurants and gourmet shops all over the world. Product quality is guaranteed by accurate selection of the raw materials used.

title: Chocolate Coconut Truffle Tea, Black Tea, Rooibos Tea, Lightly Caffeinated
description: A luscious blend of rich black tea,chocolate, coconut and Rooibos make this one sweet treat. All the taste of dessert with no calories and very low caffeine. Rich in antioxidants for your skin, brew a cup of this ndessert replacement tea and feel satisfied. As a loose leaf tea, Chocolate Coconut Truffle, will allow you to brew the tea in the traditional fashion or in your K-cup reusable filter. If you use a K-Cup you may wish to add more tea forna fuller taste. Great with a light splash of milk or heated and used like a chai.nnnnnHints for brewing a great pot of loose leaf tea:nn 1. Use filtered water. A decent cup of tea (and a lousy cup of tea) is made up with 95% water. The water taste makes a tremendous difference!nn 2. Don't over-boil your water. All the steam pouring out of your tea kettle while you're off getting the mail? It's two part hydrogen and one part oxygen,right? Water without oxygen tastes flat.nn 3. Learn the correct brewing times for the leaves you're using. Green tea, for example, cannot handle the heat of boiling water or long brewing times. If the green tea you've tasted is bitter, this is why. Brew green tea for 2 minutes at rapid steam but not the exploding steam of boiling water.nn 4. Throw away the mesh balls everyone owns and no one uses for brewing loose-leaf tea. They are only good for one cup of tea at a time. Tea leaves must have room to expand if they are going to release their flavor. Purchase a tea sock,sack, or pot with an infuser instead.

title: Skinny Crisps Low Carb and Gluten Free Crackers
description: Skinny Crisps Skinny Crisps Gluten Free, Low Carb, Vegan High Fiber Baked Soy Free No Trans Fats Dairy Free Except for Say Cheese flavor The Skinny Crisps bakery has created a nutritious, satisfying, crispy cracker that combines great taste with gluten free ingredients and approximately one half a net carb per cracker. Skinny Crisps are the perfect snack for those who need to eliminate gluten and carbohydrates from their diet and because these treats are high in fiber, they have little effect on blood sugar levels as well. Skinny Crisps contain only the highest quality ingredients including: ground almonds, chickpea flour, organic ground golden flax seed, psyllium husks, organic dehydrated cane juice, olive oil and sea salt plus spices and assorted toppings. All of these are combined to produce a tasty cracker, which can be used with dips, cheese, tuna salad and in many cases as a substitute for toast or bread. These Skinny Crisps are ideal for those with celiac disease, diabetes and low carb dieters, or just about anyone who enjoys a great cracker which is not only tasty, but healthy and nutritious. The high fiber content provides satisfaction with just a few crackers. To control hunger cravings, just have three or four crackers with some coffee or tea or juice and you may find that your hunger will subside in a few minutes. Recipe idea: Crush the Cinnamon or Brownie crisps, add a little butter, and press into a pie pan for a low carb crust.

title: Small Hand Foods Pineapple Gum Syrup - 8.5 oz
description: Simple syrup will always have its place, but sometimes you want more. Sometimes you want superior-quality gum syrup from Small Hand Foods. Gomme syrup (according to the French pronunciation) is a simple syrup substitute with pre-Prohibition origins. This premium pineapple version is made from a potent blend of organic cane sugar, gum arabic, and a pulpy pineapple infusion that lends your drink a bright acidity. Drinks made with gum syrup have a richer mouthfeel and more weighty texture than simple sugar concoctions. In other words, they're better. Don't settle for the same old syrup anymore. Upgrade your cocktail credentials with the citrusy sensation of Small Hand Foods Pineapple Gum Syrup! In stock and ready to ship. Features: Made of sugar syrup with gum arabic, a resin from the Acacia tree, and pineapple infused. A classic ingredient for pre-Prohibition cocktails. Adds more viscosity than simple syrup to create a richer mouthfeel and weightier texture. Organic cane sugar and pineapple infusion gives the syrup a golden amber color and a light acidity. A key ingredient in the San Francisco classic cocktail Pisco Punch, as well as fixes and cobblers of all kinds. . . . Specs: Size: 8 1/2 oz.

title: Shane's Sweet N' Spicy Gluten-Free Molasses Ginger Cookie - SIX PACK
description: Gluten-free Oat Flour, Cinnamon, Lemon Zest.Inspiration--and perspirationShane is the second of my three sons, but there is nothing middle about him. His mood is either sweet -- or spicy. He either loves something -- or hates it. There is nothing 'in-between' for Shane, making his boyhood read like a dogeared page out of the book on the spirited child. Did I mention that he's finicky to the point of fanatical about foodstuffs? When he was five, Shane announced that he was a 'dessert-etarian' -- dinner out meant a bun and ketchup. The upside: Shane is the perfect supertaster, so when a cookie passes his muster, it's destined to win hearts. My marching orders: a molasses cookie just like grandma's. Spicy, but not too spicy. Soft and chewy, but not too soft or chewy. No cookie compromises for Shane. Gluten-free is just a bonus.

title: Phil 'Em Up Gluten-Free Chocolate Cranberry Cookie Mix - SIX PACK
description: Fast Phil always has a lot going on. Husband, father of three, Harvard man, entrepreneur, hockey jock, musician, all around great guy. Phil does everything fast. I don't even want to know his WPM, his fingers flying to keep up with his thoughts. He can reply to a text or an email faster than I can press send. Speed has its price. The man burns through fuel like a growing teenager. So when Phil began consulting with Among Friends, he came with a warning label from his lovely wife and my good buddy Kate: Don't let him get hungry. Her words proved to be prescient, especially when fast, bread-loving Phil discovered he was gluten intolerant. Now, when Phil's energy flags, we just roll him cookies across the conference table -- slow-burning gluten-free oatmeal cookies studded with chocolate, coconut, and cranberries. title: Jerky Direct 8 Oz Buffalo TOP Sirloin (8 Steaks)
description: These high protein, low fat steaks are all natural and contain no antibiotics or added growth hormones.nnWhy eat Buffalo meat?nnIt is low calorie, low fat, low cholesterol, and it tastes great! If you didn't know what you were eating, you would probably think that it was the best beef you ever tasted. Buffalo meat is naturally flavorful and tender. You don't need to spice up buffalo with a lot of extras or hide the flavor with steak sauces. Buffalo will make any recipe better and tastes great by itself. The flavor, in most meats, is in the fat, but so are the calories, cholesterol and saturated fats. With other meats, you trim off the fat (which you paid for) and try to cook it out and drain it off. But buffalo meat is tasty without the fat. Buffalo meat is satisfying and it is concentrated.nnThat is because what you pay for is almost pure protein, 25 to 30% more than beef. It doesn't shrink in cooking, so pound for pound, it doesn't cost much more than less expensive meats. It's hard to believe, but buffalo has less fat content than even chicken, turkey, or shrimp! Due to their nature, buffalo are handled as little as possible. They spend their lives on grass, just as they always did. Their meat is not full of drugs, antibiotics, nitrites, or chemicals. Many people who have problems eating other red meats can often eat buffalo without any problems. We are now finding out what the Native Americans knew all along - Buffalo meat is for everyone, from dieters to athletes. Buffalo are no longer an endangered species. If it sounds too good to be true, it is time to find out for yourself!

title: 7.5" Retirement Edible Image Cake Toppers Decorations Personalized on Wafer Rice Paper - [Please use the 'Contact Seller' link to send us your personalized message for your topper.]
description: 7.5 inch personalized cake toppers beautifully decorated using edible food quality inks on edible rice paper.nSize: 7.5 inch round - suitable for 8 round cakes.nTo enable us to personalize your cake, please use the 'Contact Seller' link when ordering to tell us the wording for your topper (Example: 'Happy Birthday Brad').nVery easy to use - instructions are Supplied via email.nnInstructionsn1.) Cut out using dry scissors and place on your cupcakes or cake. For best results, place the toppers onto icing; can also be placed on butter cream.n2.) Ensure your icing is dry before placing a very small amount of water onto a brush or finger to fix the image down.n3.) Avoid using excessive water otherwise the moisture will make the topper shrink or tear as it absorbs water.n4.) Please note that rice paper is slightly transparent and this makes the image stand out better against lighter colored backgrounds - the image stands out best on white backgrounds so when placed onto your white icing, the colors become stronger and more vibrant.n5.) Do not refrigerate prior to use.nnCompositionn1.) Our edible wafer rice papers are made from rice paper.n2.) Ingredients: Potato Starch, Water, Vegetable Oil.nnAdditional Informationn1.) They are delivered in food grade grip seal bags. If kept in these bags, they will remain fresh for 6 - 12 months.n2.) The wafers should be kept within the grip seal bags and stored in a cool dry place.

description: Enjoy Yes! To Cookies. Most Sugar Free cookies are only sucrose free. They still contain lots of other ingredients such as starch (flour), fructose and sugar alcohols that digest into glucose (blood sugar) the same as sucrose. Fact: All starch (corn, potato, rice, soy, oat, tapioca, arrowroot, etc.) digests to sugar. Agave nectar and fructose are still sugar and deliver all the calories of sugar. All sugar alcohols are still 50% the calories of sugar, except erythritol. The sweeteners in Yes! To Cookies are stevia and erythritol which are all natural ZERO CALORIE sweeteners. Stevia and erythritol are the only all-natural sweeteners that do not digest into sugar and do not impact blood sugar. Yes! To Cookies are made from psyllium seed fiber which is not starch. Fiber does not digest into sugar so it does not impact blood sugar. Psyllium seed is highly nutritious and not just the psyllium husk used in laxatives. Most people need more fiber in their diet and need to reduce sugar. Erythritol and stevia do not cause the bloating and laxative effect of foods sweetened with other sugar alcohols such maltitol, sorbitol, xylitol, etc.nnYes! To Cookies are a worry free treat to satisfy snack cravings with fiber that helps you to feel full. Either before a meal to reduce appetite with fiber to eat less, after meals to satisfy a sweet tooth without added sugar and increased sugar cravings, or as an in between meal snack or meal replacement with lots of fiber to feel full. Yes! To Cookies is the 1st TRULY sugar free, gluten free, all-natural, delicious healthy treat that you can enjoy guilt and worry free, and share with family and friends. MUST BE KEPT FROZEN

description: Buy Premium Quality Poppy Seeds only from Food-To-Live and SOLD by Food-To-Live. BEWARE of imitations - we believe in quality seeds.nnNutty and pleasant in taste, poppy seeds are nutritious oilseeds used as condiment in cooking. They are the seeds obtained from the dry fruits (pods) of the poppy plant (opium poppy) and entirely free from any sinister side effects of other poppy plant products such as opium poppy.nnPoppy, in general, is used either, in the form of whole seeds, ground or as thick or thin paste in recipes. Poppy applied over toasts, breads, seafood before they are deep-fried. In India and Pakistan, gently fried seeds are ground to a make thin paste, which is then added as thickening in dips, curries and in sweet dishes. In South India, poppy seed milk is used to prepare sweet recipe popular as kuskus payasam with added milk, coconut milk, cardamom, raisins, and sugar. In Central Europe, especially in Austria and Hungary, the seeds are used in s a popular sweet pastry dish like Strudel and Germknodel. The seeds are widely used in confectionery like stuffing, rolls, bagels, sweet breads, biscuits, and cakes.

title: Lucy's Cookies, Pumpkin Patch, 5.5 Ounce
description: When Dr. Lucy Gibney learned her child had severe food allergies, she got down to some serious medical research in the kitchen. Inspired by her son and encouraged by her husband, she put aside her career as an emergency physician to create great tasting foods for people with modified diets. She started by taking her mother’s time tested recipes and substituted her own gluten free flour blend. Next she meticulously experimented until she baked great tasting cookies without milk, butter or eggs. Most importantly, she knew the only way to make products in a protected environment and prevent unwanted ingredients such as peanuts or tree nuts was to control the process from start to finish. She has put all of her efforts into creating a dedicated bakery where her vision is now a reality. Today, Lucy's cookies stand as proof that no one ever has to be denied a good cookie. Every crispy, crunchy Lucy's cookie is baked without wheat, gluten, milk, eggs, peanuts or tree nuts. But you'd never know it. They taste delicious. Today, Dr. Lucy continues to advocate for people with food allergies and special diets. Her vision unfolds daily with increasing demand for her yummy cookies and enthusiastic support from dedicated customers. Made from natural ingredients using no preservatives or trans-fat, and high quality ingredients are used in a carefully controlled bakery to be sure the products meet tight allergen testing criteria. Lucy’s has four classic flavors: chocolate chip, oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon. 100 to 120 calories per serving. Vegan and Kosher Pareve certified.

title: El Guapo Gumbo Bitters - tastes just like gumbo!
description: Remember you can't always trust reviews in a public forum. So what to do? We made it easy for you. Want to see some professional reviews and opinions on our products? Check out our homepage for that And also check out our Facebook, Twitter, and the recipes page on our site to learn how to use them!nnwww.elguapobitters.com n nPrimary flavors include; Creole Tomato, Celery, Green Onion, Bell Pepper, Cayenne Pepper, Mirliton, Celery, Thyme, with additional herbs & spices.nnAt El Guapo we only use whole ingredients. No extracts, essential oils, or artificial flavorings are added to any of our products. We extract concentrated flavor from fresh fruits, vegetables, herbs, and spices. We source all ingredients locally grown (New Orleans) if available. Other items are chosen as close as we can to ensure the most regional product we can make.nnBitters are the backbone and seasoning of a cocktail. When you think of food, if you don't put salt or pepper other seasonings on your food it tastes flat, one-dimensional. That's the function bitters serve in a cocktail. They do bring subtle flavors to the drink, but the main function is they act as a flavor enhancer. They amplify and bring out the flavor of the other ingredients and liquors. nnBitters also can provide the same function when added to food recipes. Try them in sauces, soups, marinades, salsas, and condiments.nnOur bitters are primarily glycerin based. We extract flavor from ingredients in 3 ways glycerin, alcohol, and water. We remove most of the alcohol before bottling. This allows us to give you a more concentrated and varied level of flavor than using only 1 extraction method. While there is little alcohol to carry aromas out of the bottle when you smell, once you add it to an alcoholic beverage it blooms and all the aroma emerges. Our bitters are designed to be able to be used by everyone and for a variety of applications.

Haribo, founded in 1920 in Bonn, Germany by Hans Riegel, is one of the most prominent manufacturers of sweets (namely fruit gums, licorice, and foam) in the world. The company name is an acronym for Hans Riegel, Bonn and stands as a reminder of Haribo's continuing loyalty to early traditions. After Hans Riegel died during World War II, his son, also named Hans Riegel, took over the factory and expanded its operations, taking over many local confectionery manufacturers in countries all over the world. Currently, Haribo operates five factories in Germany and 13 throughout the rest of Europe. The company also has sales offices in almost every country in Europe as well as in the Unites States. Haribo's German catch phrase is Haribo macht kinder froh / und Erwachsene ebenso, which translates as Kids and grown-ups love it so / the happy world of Haribo.

title: Haribo Gummi Peaches & Gummi Strawberries & Cream, 5oz Bags in a Gift Box (Pack of 4)
description: A new pairing of two of the most popular fruit-flavored gummies, now in a gift box for any occasion. Haribo, founded in 1920 in Bonn, Germany by Hans Riegel, is one of the most prominent manufacturers of sweets (namely fruit gums, licorice, and foam) in the world. The company name is an acronym for Hans Riegel, Bonn and stands as a reminder of Haribo's continuing loyalty to early traditions. After Hans Riegel died during World War II, his son, also named Hans Riegel, took over the factory and expanded its operations, taking over many local confectionery manufacturers in countries all over the world. Currently, Haribo operates five factories in Germany and 13 throughout the rest of Europe. The company also has sales offices in almost every country in Europe as well as in the Unites States. Haribo's German catch phrase is Haribo macht kinder froh / und Erwachsene ebenso, which translates as Kids and grown-ups love it so / the happy world of Haribo.

title: Bonomo Turkish Taffy Bar, Banana, 1.5 Ounce (Pack of 24)
description: Tired of your average, boring candy? Try Bonomo. The vintage candy you can smack, crack and enjoy. If you're like a lot of Baby Boomers, you have a relentless craving for all things vintage: vintage cars, vintage music and vintage movies, to name just a few items. In many cases, they just don't make things the way they used to. Bonomo still uses a 100-year old process of making taffy that is smooth, rich and tastes like no other taffy in the world. Ever since the 1930s when the Bonomo family purchased Turkish Chewing Taffy from candy manufacturer H. Schwarz and Sons, the name Bonomo has been synonymous with authentic Turkish taffy treats. Since acquiring the brand in 2002, entrepreneurs Kenny Wiesen and Jerry Sweeney have strived to make Bonomo a retro candy that's true to its original form. You'll enjoy the same unique candy treat that's hard enough to smack and crack, but soft enough to stretch.

title: Bella Lucia Pizzelle Cookies, Lemon Love
description: Bella Lucia was launched in my home kitchen in 2009 never realizing it would become the company that it is today.After being diagnosed with celiac disease in 2004 and tasting the quality of cookies that were available I knew that there must be a better way to make a better cookie.My favorite cookie when I was growing up was the pizzella, a Italian waffle cookie my Mom would make one at a time on an iron that was placed right on the stove burner. Thus the name 'Bella Lucia' translating Beautiful Lucy after my late Mother. We believe that by combining the traditional taste with the new dietary needs that integrity of my Italian heritage remains intact.Bella Lucia prides ourselves with the traditional taste and flavor that merges it with new dietary needs that has become all too common.Lots of people ask, what else does your company make besides pizzelle? The truth is, we could make most anything, however, we believe if you want to do something right, you focus on one thing at a time till its perfect!We want you to enjoy our pizzelle cookies as much as we do and we are confident that you'll love our pizzelle and be back for more!

description: Nougat (Latin Nux Gatum)has very distance origins. it is found mentioned in Arab manuscripts in the 12th century. Known as haloua or halwa (halva). But even earlier, Phoenicians spread the recipe as far as Turkey and Greece, Italy, Spain and more. In the Middle Ages, the white Nougat made in Marseille is famous and soon the entire Provence region and the South East of France starts making it. The most famous one is from Montelimar. The main ingredients are almonds, honey, stiffly beaten egg whites (where the characteristic white color comes from). For more than half a century, the Carlier family guarded a closely held family recipe to make traditional nougat of the very highest quality. Today it is still solely based on the subtle combination of nuts, pure honey, egg white and pure sugar. This all-natural blend of flavor and sweet is made with only authentic ingredients like delicious California Almonds, pistachios, Turkish hazelnuts, dried fruits like berries and cranberries and real bees honey. Combine that pureness with Belgian premium artisanal quality and know-how and it is no surprise why Carlier Nougat is so enjoyed all over the world. This is a 12 piece gift bag, great small anytime gift!

title: Bob's Red Mill Arrowroot Starch Flour, 16 oz
description: Arrowroot is a large perennial herb (Maranta arundinacea) found in rainforest habitats. The herb is cultivated for a starch obtained from the rhizomes (rootstock), which is also called arrowroot. It is a thickening agent that may be used as a one-for-one replacement for cornstarch. As a thickener, it can be used for soups, sauces and puddings. It has no flavor of its own and is the easiest starch to digest. It is also an excellent ingredient for gluten free baking or breading and creates a softer and lighter texture to cakes and breads. Our all natural Arrowroot Starch is not irradiated and contains no added sulfites.

Extremely effective at low use levels in forming gels (0.05 %), fine mesh, low acyl and forms hard, non elastic, brittle gels and fluid gels. It is recommended for dry mixes and high solid applications.

title: 4mular Xanthan Gum, 20 Ounce
description: Xanthan gum (Keltrol T630) by 4mular, renowned for its pure ingredients and superb quality among professional chefs in the restaurant/foodservice industry. This special xanthan gum has enhanced properties, such as viscosity, acid stability and galactomannan synergy. It is used as a thickener in sauces, as an agent in ice cream that prevents ice crystals from forming and as a fat substitute that adds the mouth feel of fat without the calories. This xanthan gum type is the most flexible and resistant to salt and acidity. It achieves higher viscosities and better acid stability at elevated temperatures than other xanthan gums. It is 80 mesh and transparent, so the final product is clear, not cloudy.

description: In 1868, Jean Tobler(Theodor Tobler's father) owned his own confectionery shop in Bern, Switzerland, producing chocolate confectionery from products supplied by other manufacturers. nIn 1899, Demand for Tobler's chocolate products was so great that Jean Tobler founded a chocolate factory of his own. title: Quaranta (5 pack) Assorted Nut Torrone Bars 5 x100g Soft Torrone Nougat from Italy
description: You will receive 2 bars of Hazelnut, 2 bars of Almond and 1 bar of Dark Chocolate with almond & hazelnut nougat bar.nnTorrone, otherwise known as nougat, is a concoction made from honey, well-whipped egg whites, vanilla, and various nuts. it is an ancient sweet that requires considerable skill and care to make well, and in the past was also a great favorite among pastry chefs because it can be used as a building material for making fanciful cakes and other such delights. It's made throughout Italy.nnWay back in 1924, over three generations ago, the company Quaranta 's Confectionery Industry started its history in the town of Caravaggio in the province of Bergamo. The founder, Antonio Quaranta and his wife Alzira, dedicated themselves to the production of handmade nougat and some other traditional sweets typical of Bergamo and Cremona. Production was situated in the first floor of their house, in Vittorio Emanuele Street, located in the heart of Caravaggio's hystorical center. Quaranta's son, Enrico Quaranta, moved the operation into a new factory in the early 70's. This move was made with special care to preserve the old memories and special handcrafted care that have distinguished all of Quaranta's products (especially nougats) from the beginning.nToday the business is still managed by Quaranta's family through the founder's nephews, Massimo and Fabio Quaranta, in an innovative 6,000 square meter factory, furnished with the most efficient production and quality check instruments.

title: Lindt Lindor Truffles White Chocolate, 30-count in a Gift Box
description: The Lindt DifferencennCreating fine chocolate is an art that requires great skill, dedication and passion. The Master Chocolatiers of Lindt are experts of this craft. For more than 165 years, Lindt has been developing innovative chocolate recipes with meticulous craftsmanship, resulting in superior tasting, high quality premium chocolate.nnLindt Chocolate uses only the finest ingredients, and is one of the few chocolate manufacturers that control the entire production process - from roasting the cacao beans to producing the chocolate.nnnThe Lindt StorynnIn 1845, confectioner David Sprngli-Schwarz and his inventive son, Rudolf Sprungli-Ammann, owned a small confectionary shop in the Marktgasse of Zurich's Old Town. They dared to try something new- a fashionable new recipe from Italy for manufacturing chocolate in solid form.nnIn 1879, Rodolphe Lindt, one of the most famous chocolate-makers of his day, developed a technique by which he could manufacture chocolate unique to others in aroma and melting characteristics. Lindt used the conche he had invented to produce chocolate with delicate flavor. His melting chocolate soon achieved fame, and contributed significantly to the worldwide reputation of Swiss chocolate.nnIt was in 1899 that Sprngli's private company Chocolat Sprngli acquired the small but famous chocolate factory of Rodolphe Lindt in Berne. This brave step transferred not only the factory but also the manufacturing secrets and the Rodolphe Lindt brand name to the young Sprngli company which now changed its name to Lindt & Sprngli.nnIn 1986, Lindt & Sprngli (USA) Inc., was activated and a manufacturing site and administration building were commissioned in Stratham, New Hampshire where it has expanded and successfully operates today.

It helps ingredients blend more effectively and stay blended while waiting on a shelf. For example - water and oil mixtures, as well as bits of spice in a salad dressing.nn Xanthan gum is also used as a thickener. Add a bit to water and it becomes more viscous. Many fat free salad dressing maintain and oily viscosity by using thickeners such as xanthan gum. In pastry fillings, it prevents the water seeping out and soaking the dough, thus protecting the crispness of the crust.nn Xanthan gum is used in ice creams as well to prevent the formation of ice crystals and keep the product smooth.nn Xanthan gum has become popular in the gluten free circles. It helps give the dough a sticky consistency.nn Only a small amount of xanthan gum is necessary to achieve the desired result, usually less than 0.5% of the food product weight. nn Nutritionally, xanthan gum is a carbohydrate with 7 grams of fiber per tablespoon.

title: Arrowroot Powder 16 Ounces (1 Pound)
description: From Wikipedia:nnArrowroot makes clear, shimmering fruit gels and prevents ice crystals from forming in homemade ice cream. It can also be used as a thickener for acidic foods, such as Asian sweet and sour sauce. It is used in cooking to produce a clear, thickened sauce, such as a fruit sauce. It will not make the sauce go cloudy, like cornstarch, flour or other starchy thickening agents would.nnThe lack of gluten in arrowroot flour makes it useful as a replacement for wheat flour in some baking uses. Like other pure starches, however, arrowroot is almost pure carbohydrates and devoid of protein, thus it does not provide a complete substitute for wheat flour for bread-making, which requires gluten.nnArrowroot thickens at a lower temperature than flour or cornstarch, is not weakened by acidic ingredients, has a more neutral taste, and is not affected by freezing. It doesn't mix well with dairy, forming a slimy mixture. It is recommended that arrowroot be mixed with a cool liquid before adding to a hot fluid. The mixture should be heated only until the mixture thickens and removed immediately to prevent the mixture from thinning. Overheating tends to break down arrowroot's thickening property. Two teaspoons of arrowroot can be substituted for one tablespoon of cornstarch, or one teaspoon of arrowroot for one tablespoon of wheat flour.

title: Gourmet Semisweet Chocolate Covered Pistachios (1.5 pounds) by Nut Roaster's Reserve
description: We start with the freshest whole pistachios, carefully roasted to perfection and let them cool overnight. Then we load 150 pounds of them in a chocolate pan, drizzling them with chocolate as the drum turns until each nut is coated with a thick layer of chocolate. This takes about 1-1/2 hours and is exacting work. Once the chocolate layer is ready, we load the entire batch into a ribbed finishing pan for another half an hour to give these nuts their glossy finish. We end up with a spectacular product - chocolate covered pistachios!

title: Chocolate Peanuts (32 ounces) by Nut Roaster's Reserve

This takes about 1-1/2 hours and is exacting work. Once the chocolate layer is ready, we load the entire batch into a ribbed finishing pan for another half an hour to give these nuts their glossy finish. The truffles used are the distinguished gourmet truffles from Alba, a town in the Piedmont region of Italy. The company name is an acronym for Hans Riegel, Bonn and stands as a reminder of Haribo's continuing loyalty to early traditions. After Hans Riegel died during World War II, his son, also named Hans Riegel, took over the factory and expanded its operations, taking over many local confectionery manufacturers in countries all over the world. description: The goal at Jackson's Honest Potato Chips is to bring the potato chip back to its humble and simple roots by using the finest organic potatoes available and kettle frying them by hand using organic coconut oil. But we also use it because it gives our chips the best flavor and crunch. Industrially processed polyunsaturated vegetable oils just don't cut it anymore: try a chip cooked the way they were meant to be, in coconut oil. It will change your potato chip expectations forever. title: Fresh White Bianchetto Truffles 2 Ounce
description: Bianchetto truffles, also known as Blanquette, Marzuolo (March in Italian) or Spring Truffles, are a less expensive substitute for White truffles (Tuber Magnatum Pico) found in the same region. The season for Bianchetto Truffles typically runs from early January through April. The aroma of Bianchetto truffles is similar to the much more expensive White Alba or Perigord truffle, although has a little more of a garlicky bite. At maturity, the exterior of the Bianchetto truffle turns light to reddish brown with irregular dark brown patches. Inside, the truffle becomes tawny to dark brown, interlaced with a network of white veins. Bianchetto truffles range in size from hazelnut to golf ball sized. Bianchetto Truffles can be used in many recipes calling for White truffles.Fresh Bianchetto Truffles can last up to two weeks when refrigerated, but they should be used as soon as possible - the fresher, the better!

title: Anthony's Arrowroot Powder (Flour), 5 Pounds (5lb Bulk), 100% Gluten Free
description: For over 7,000 years, Arrowroot Powder has been used by indigenous Caribbean tribes as a highly digestible starch in traditional Caribbean recipes.nnThe lack of gluten in Arrowroot Flour (powder) makes it a perfect replacement for wheat and corn based flours. Due to it's pure starch nature, Arrowroot thickens at a lower temperature than cornstarch or conventional flour. This causes Arrowroot Flour to have a more neutral taste and very smooth consistency. nnOur Arrowroot is derived from the rhizomes of the Maranta Arundinacea plant, found in the Caribbean island of St. Vincent. The Arrowroot itself is picked, washed, and cleaned of its undesirable scales. The roots are then reduced to a pulp using large mortars, and then dried, allowing the insoluble liquids of the root to evaporate. What's left is our pure unadulterated Anthony's Arrowroot Powder.nnWait, what's that you say? You don't have any cooking needs for our Arrowroot Powder? Well perhaps you have recently been struck by a poisonous arrow and are seeking to treat your wound. Of course you are, and no doubt you've come to the right place. As the old saying goes, When you get hit by a poisonous arrow, goto Amazon.com and search for Anthony's Arrowroot Powder. I know, my mother used to say it all the time as well. It has been suggested that the name Arrowroot was derived by a practice of ancient Caribbean tribes that used the liquid of the root as a dressing on poison-arrow wounds, as it draws out the poison when applied to the site of the injury. nnHowever, as common as poisonous arrow wounds have become these days, we would definitely recommend using Anthony's Arrowroot Powder primarily for baking purposes, and not so much for poisonous arrow wound purposes.

description: Gluten allergies make for some tough food choices when food shopping. Bread, cookies and anything made with wheat flour is off the table, which makes baking nearly impossible. What a good thing MILLIARD Arrowroot Flour isn't made from wheat! Arrowroot is actually a tropical plant that was once used centuries ago to treat poison-arrow wounds. The starch in its roots is highly absorbent and would be used to draw out poison and other toxins. In our present-day, the roots are harvested, dried and ground into powder that can be used much like typical wheat flour and has similar properties. Make gravy thicker, bake muffins, fry pancakes and enjoy baked goods again! title: "The Plan" Friendly Three Pack Flax-Granola
description: Four years ago we met with Lyn Genet and developed the Plan Friendly Flax Granola that she recommends to her clients to this day. There are NO OTHER Flax-Granolas on the market who can make this claim. Only IMITATORS selling untested versions of what we originated.nIf you're on the Plan or thinking about trying The Plan, you only need these three 12 ounce bags (approx. 9 cups). And, with the variety pack, you can try all three of our Plan Friendly flax-granolas and determine your favorite.nEven if you're not on The Plan, our Flax-Granola has changed lives. This amazing cereal or topping is very low in carbohydrates, making it ideal for anyone who wants to limit their intake of starches and sugars. The combination of healthy fats, high fiber, and antioxidants found in our flax-granola make it a great choice for weight control, detox, cleanse and a healthy internal balance.nAccording to Sally Lee, Executive Editor of Ladies Home Journal, our Flax-Granola helped her lower her cholesterol by over 50 points (LHJ 2/14 p 6).nFlax is one of the best sources of Omega-3 oils found anywhere. These good fats fight inflammation throughout your body. When left unchecked, inflammation can lead to many chronic illnesses including; heart disease, arthritis, irritable bowel, diabetes, and even some cancers.nThe big mistake the other flax-granolas make is to add ground flax. We only use whole flaxseed in our flax granola. Milled or ground flax is rendered worthless as oxidation destroys flax's beneficial oils in a matter of minutes. That is why chewing flax is the best way to release the essential benefits of flax and you WILL chew our flax-granola.nAnd now, we're offering a genuine deal - our variety three pack including one 12 ounce bag of Fruit & Berry, one 12 oz bag of Apple Cinnamon, and one 12 oz bag of our newest variety, Pumpkin Spice for only $37.75 and that INCLUDES shipping!

title: Redwood Trails Beef Jerky - Chinese Peking (3 X 3.25 Oz Bags)
description: Redwood Trails Beef Jerky is an artisan beef jerky company that prides itself in being the first to use wine in it's marinate. This evolutionary concept, that is attracting people back to jerky as a part of their healthy diet, comes naturally from the influences and abundance of the Northern California Wine Country in which we reside. The high quality of our product comes from a superior grade of protein and natural ingredients, no preservatives nor nitrates, and we have removed up to a third of sodium as compared to the leading brands. Redwood Trails Beef Jerky has exchanged salt for its unique flavor profiles. nOur jerky represents a marriage of old world technique with a twenty-first century understanding of healthy curing and proper handling of our meat. We have set a higher standard in the beef jerky industry first by the quality of our meat by using USDA Choice Top Round of Beef. Secondly, we hand carve all our meat, cutting against the grain to create a tenderness in each piece not matched by others. Thirdly, the beef is marinated for a week in the freshest of ingredients and wines of Sonoma and Napa Valley to impart each piece with an intense delicate flavor. Next comes a slow smoking over real hickory wood for hours to infuse a flavor that just cannot be duplicated with those artificially created Natural Smoke Flavoring used by the Big Guys. nThe moment you open the bag, smell the tempting hickory bouquet as it embraces all your senses, up until you have finished the last tender bite of jerky, you will understand why we take the time to prepare everything in a certain way without cutting cornernIf you enjoy the salty, shoe leathery stuff that gives jerky its original name, then we are not that jerky! However, if a tender, savory and flavorful piece of meat appeals to you? Then we have the product for you. Redwood Trails Beef Jerky is so addictive to your pallet you will have a hard time putting it down, especially once the package is open.

title: Mayan Caveman Cookies
description: Mayan Caveman Cookies are made with ingredients cavemen (living in Mesoamerica!) would have had access to! They combine the South American flavors of chocolate and chili, with the power of the ancient superfood chia. There are 8 delicious Caveman Cookies per package.FAQS1. What are the ingredients of Mayan Caveman Cookies?Mayan Caveman Cookies are made with organic honey, almond meal, raw cacao powder, cashews, chia seeds, pure vanilla extract, cinnamon and chili powder. That's it! There are no other hidden ingredients.2. What kind of honey do you use?We use organic honey that is certified by True Source Honey to come only from reliable, ethical and quality sources.3. Are the cookies peanut-free?Yes! They are peanut-free and produced in a peanut-free facility.4. Are your cookies gluten-free?Yes! Our cookies are made entirely with gluten-free ingredients. While they are produced in a facility that uses wheat, we take care to protect against cross-contamination and test our products to make sure they fall well within federal guidelines.5. How long will my cookies last?Honey is a natural preservative, so our products have a shelf life of one year. However, to keep your cookies chewy and delicious, we recommend that you store them at room-temperature and in a dry location.6. What size are your cookies?Mayan Caveman Cookies are approximately half an ounce each. Their diameter varies between 2.25 to 2.75 depending on how they spread in the oven.7. Will these cookies help me lose weight?Well, we are not going to guarantee anything, but Caveman Cookies are an excellent way to satisfy your sweet tooth while also getting protein and fiber, which help you feel full. Oh... and we have it on good authority that cavemen had very attractive figures ;-)

title: Cadbury Finger Tin Assortment, 13.2 Ounce Tin (2 pack)
description: In 1824, John Cadbury opened a grocer's shop at 93 Bull Street, Birmingham in the 1830's. Among other things, he sold cocoa and drinking chocolate, which he prepared himself using a pestle and mortar. The Cadbury manufacturing business was born in 1831, when John Cadbury decided to start producing on a commercial scale and bought a four-story warehouse in nearby Crooked Lane. The first Cadbury Easter egg was made in 1875. The earliest eggs were made with dark chocolate and had a smooth, plain surface. They were filled with sugar-coated chocolate drops known as 'dragees'. Later Easter eggs were decorated and had their plain shells enhanced with chocolate piping and marzipan flowers. In 1904, George Cadbury Jr. was given the challenge to develop a milk chocolate bar with more milk than anything else on the market. At first, Cadbury resisted creating an alkalized cocoa (a product made less bitter by adding harmless carbonate of potash) having emphasized the purity of their own cocoa. But, eventually, the company realized that alkalized cocoa was the future and created Bournville Cocoa. Cadbury Dairy Milk started out in pale mauve with red script, in a continental style 'parcel wrap' at its launch in 1905. The full Dairy Milk range became purple and gold in 1920.

title: Rowntrees Fruit Gums (Amazon 6-Pack) - British
description: Rowntree's Fruit Gumsare circular sweets formerly made byRowntree's, who were later acquired byNestl. They appear in different colours, each with a different flavour: strawberry, orange, lemon, blackcurrant and lime. The sweets were first introduced in 1893, and originally marketed as Rowntree's Clear Gums - The nation's favourite sweet - and were available in twopenny tubes and sixpenny packets.[1]They are primarily composed ofglucose syrupandfruitjuices and are as a result similar to wine gums. In addition to the traditional roll packaging, they come in a larger volume box, that contains the sweets in the shape of the fruit or part of the fruit that the flavour represents. Originally the purple fruit gums were blueberry, but this changed to blackcurrant in the 1990s.
